---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
import Link from '../components/Link.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import thumbsup from "../assets/images/thumbsup.png";
---
<MainLayout title="Titel">
	<div class="grid grid-cols-5">
		<div class="col-span-1">
			<header class="fixed top-0 bottom-0">
				<a href="#hero"><img class="w-[300px] p-[65px]" src="3dlogoglowcopy.png" alt="logo"></a>
				<ul>
					<li>
						<a href="#inspo">Inspiration</a>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a href="#showcase">Showcase</a>
					</li>
					<li>
						<a href="#process">Process</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			</header>
		</div>
	
		<div class="col-span-3">
			
				<section id="hero">
					<img src="hero.jpg" alt="">
				</section>
			
			
				<section id="inspo">
					<p>Expert Ment is a unique font born from a happy typoâ€”an "experiment" gone wonderfully wrong. Inspired by the pixelated fonts of old-school computer screens, it blends the structured simplicity of early digital text with the flowing elegance of cursive writing.</p>
					<img src="insp1.png" alt="insp">
					<img src="insp2.png" alt="insp">
				</section>
			
				
				<section id="homage">
					<p>This font pays homage to a time when every pixel mattered, capturing the charm of retro tech while adding a playful, modern twist. Perfectly imperfect, Expert Ment invites you to embrace the beauty of creative accidents.</p>
					<img src="decorative.png" alt="">
				</section>
			
			
				<section id="showcase">
					<p>Here's how Expert Ment brings cursive to the digital grid. Explore the pixel-perfect alphabet that fuses retro tech vibes with handwritten elegance:</p>
					<img src="horse.jpg" alt="">
					<img src="cover.webp" alt="">
				</section>
			
			
				<section id="process">
					<p>Expert Ment began with the elegant font Nautica, which I pixelized in Photoshop to capture a retro feel. After vectorizing the pixelated letters in Illustrator, I used Calligraphr to turn them into a functional font.</p>
					<img src="aplhabet.png" alt="">
					<img src="calgrph.png" alt="">
				</section>
			
		</div>
	</div>
